Comment: I spend the first half of the game slowly picking apart his defenses on the right hand (with even trades) not gaining any leeway points-wise, but making  slow progress toward opening  up the castle, and snatching the throne. But in the  end a dang horse shifts the balance of the game, with a rather magnificent fork on the part of my opponent, which is immediately compounded by a stupid greedy move on my part, resulting in a queen for queen trade. When the dominoes fall nothing is left for me. (Thanks ionadowman for helping me analyze my many mistakes.)
